To ensure the search bar animations (the rotating border and glow effects) only occur when the user interacts with the component, I will modify the CSS in `RetroSearchInput`.

### Specification of Changes

1.  **Pause Animations by Default**: The `retro-spin` animation on the gradient layers will be set to `paused` initially.
2.  **Activate on Hover/Focus**: The animations will switch to `running` only when the user hovers over the search bar or focuses on the input field.
3.  **Dynamic Glow Visibility**: The outer "glow" effect (`.retro-glow`) will be hidden (opacity 0) by default and will fade in only during interaction, making the component look cleaner when idle.

