Here is the specification and implementation to add full Admin CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) and Visibility toggling to the Premium Payloads section.

### **Specification**

1.  **Database (SQL)**:
    *   A new table `payloads` to store the data dynamically.
    *   RLS policies to ensure only admins can modify data, while verified users can read visible payloads.

2.  **UI/UX Updates (`ResourcesPage.tsx`)**:
    *   **Admin Mode**: If `user.role === 'admin'`, extra controls appear.
    *   **Add Button**: A prominent "Add Payload" button appears in the header when the "Premium Payloads" tab is active.
    *   **Card Controls**: Each payload card gets a toolbar (visible only to admins) with:
        *   **Edit**: Opens a modal to modify code/description.
        *   **Visibility**: Toggles an Eye/Eye-Slash icon. When hidden (`is_visible: false`), the card becomes semi-transparent and is hidden from non-admins.
        *   **Delete**: Triggers a confirmation modal to remove the payload.
    *   **Editor Modal**: A sleek, dark-themed modal to input Title, Category, Code, and Description.
    *   **Filtering**: Non-admins will strictly see only `is_visible: true` items.

### **SQL Query**

Run this in your Supabase SQL Editor to set up the backend:

```sql
-- 1. Create the Payloads table
create table public.payloads (
  id uuid default gen_random_uuid() primary key,
  title text not null,
  category text not null,
  code text not null,
  description text,
  is_visible boolean default true,
  created_at timestamp with time zone default timezone('utc'::text, now()) not null,
  updated_at timestamp with time zone default timezone('utc'::text, now())
);

-- 2. Enable RLS
alter table public.payloads enable row level security;

-- 3. Policies
-- Everyone (authenticated) can see visible payloads
create policy "Visible payloads are viewable by everyone"
  on public.payloads for select
  using ( is_visible = true );

-- Admins can see ALL payloads (even hidden ones)
create policy "Admins can see all payloads"
  on public.payloads for select
  using ( 
    auth.jwt() ->> 'email' = 'ragow49@gmail.com' -- Replace with your admin check logic or specific email
  );

-- Only Admins can insert/update/delete
create policy "Admins can insert payloads"
  on public.payloads for insert
  with check ( auth.jwt() ->> 'email' = 'ragow49@gmail.com' );

create policy "Admins can update payloads"
  on public.payloads for update
  using ( auth.jwt() ->> 'email' = 'ragow49@gmail.com' );

create policy "Admins can delete payloads"
  on public.payloads for delete
  using ( auth.jwt() ->> 'email' = 'ragow49@gmail.com' );
```

